Steps to install Mysql on Ubuntu 24

Install mysql
=============

apt-get update && apt-get upgrade

apt-get install mysql-server

systemctl start mysql

systemctl enable mysql

Secure MySQL & Set Root Password
==========
mysql_secure_installation	//It will prompt you to set a root password, follow the recommended security settings.

vi /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf

bind-address = 0.0.0.0

Then restart mysql service

systemctl status mysql.servvice

systemctl restart mysql.servvice




